                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>At their meetings in New York, September 12–18, the Foreign Ministers of the
                    United States, France, and the United Kingdom, agreed, <hi rend="italic">inter
                        alia</hi>, to increase and reinforce their forces in Europe, treat any
                    attack on Berlin or the Federal Republic as an attack on themselves, and “permit
                    the establishment of mobile police formations organized on a <hi rend="italic"
                        >Land</hi> basis but with provisions which would enable the Federal
                    Government to have adequate powers to make effective use of all or part of this
                    force in order to meet the exigencies of the present situation.” For further
                    documentation on the Foreign Ministers meetings, including the text of the
                    communiqué on Germany, see <ref target="frus1950v03#pg_1108">volume III, pages
                        1108</ref> ff.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
